 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
               LegSem LegStar Schemagen Eclipse plugin Version 1.0.1
                                   Release Notes
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PREREQUISITES:

 This plugin requires Eclipse 3.2.1. It uses the LegStar Schemagen module which in turn
 relies on Ant.
 
 You must install the Legstar Schemagen module before you can use this Eclipse plugin.
 
 The Legstar Schemagen module can be downloaded from http://www.legsem.com/legstar/schemagen.
 
 The Schemagen Eclipse Plugin also requires the LegStar Common Eclipse plugin. For
 intructions on how to install the Common Eclipse Plugin, see http://www.legsem.com/legstar/common-plugin.
 
INSTALLING/UNINSTALLING:

 [[1]] Ensure that the base Schemagen module has been installed and that the folder holding native
    libraries has been added to the search PATH.
    
 [[2]] Within Eclipse, create a remote site using:
 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Help-->Software Updates-->Find and Install-->Search for new features-->New Remote site.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  
  Have the URL point to http://www.legsem.com/legstar/eclipse/update and select the
    LegStar Schema Generator feature.

 [[3]] Restart Eclipse and check that "LegsStar Schema Generator" shows up in:
 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Help-->About Eclipse SDK-->Plug-in details.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   
 [[4]] Start the plugin from the Legstar menu or the toolbar button.
   
 [[5]] To uninstall, use:

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Help-->Software Updates-->Manage Configurations.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  then right-click on the feature you wish to uninstall.

